<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8422] Incorrect properties copy in Sql.newInstance </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8422</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The constructor `Properties(Properties defaults)` does not create a copy, but a new object with the argument as defaults. That breaks JDBC drivers that expect the properties to be present in the object directly (enumerating of keys, containsKey etc.).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13126901">GROOVY-8422</key>
